# LED Blink Project (Arduino)

## Project Title
LED Blink Project using Arduino Uno

## Hardware Required
- Arduino Uno  
- LED  
- 220Ω Resistor  
- Breadboard  
- Jumper Wires  
- USB Cable  

## Circuit Diagram Description
LED is connected to digital pin 13 of Arduino through a 220Ω resistor. The cathode of LED is connected to GND pin.

## How to Upload Code
1. Open Arduino IDE  
2. Connect Arduino Uno via USB  
3. Select Board (Arduino Uno)  
4. Select COM port  
5. Write or paste code  
6. Click Upload  

## Expected Output
LED will blink ON and OFF repeatedly every 1 second.

## Troubleshooting Tips
- Check LED polarity (long leg positive)  
- Verify correct COM port selection  
- Ensure USB cable and board connection
